level 1, no mana, reagent = friendly personality.<br>
<br>
Have not lfg'd in over a year.  Would like to solo sometimes but I don't want to turn down my friends when they ask to group.  NO ability will make LFG'ing any easier, having friends means you won't have to do it.  <br>
Find friends, group with them regularly, enjoy the game more.<br>
<br>
Lascaris <br>
Wizzie of 56 seasons<br>
Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aphasia>Aphasia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/01 10:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can we get an enhancment that helps us get groups?</span><hr size=1> *NO ability will make LFG'ing any easier, having friends means you won't have to do it. *<br>
<br>
No ability will make LFGing (getting a group) any easier? tell that to a cleric or enchanter sometime. Why is it that when I play my wizard i can be LFG for hours, but if I play my shadowknight I usually only have to shout LFG once? I'm the same person in both characters. Having a bunch of online friends is a great way to have groups, in fact its how i have most of my groups, but it certainly isnt reliable.<br>
<br>
I think what is called for is an even playing field for finding groups.  If your picking a football team for a pickup game, do you pick the quarterback or the kicker first? <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzatty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zatty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 8:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Can we get an enhancment that helps us get groups?</span><hr size=1> Only a dramatic increase in damage will help get us grouped in Kunark and Velious.  Of course no one goes to Velious for pickup groups post 50 at this point so that is moot.<br>
<br>
We are beating a dead horse here folks.  VI fears the power that Wizards should have in the first place.  Melee's were and still are jealous of the fact that we can solo and they cannot...  So they bumped up the power of the Melee in Kunark.  Sigh... the poor warrior in full DW with a Fungi still cannot solo.  What shall we do?  <br>
<br>
I know..  let's further inflate the game!  More power to Wizards and Mages!  Give Necro's an AOE lifetap with Mem Blur built in.  Druids and Shaman should have resurrection!  Clerics should have their sprinklers handed to them by their trainers at 55.  OR... tone down the mobs and nerf the melees damage over time to a point where all classes do the same amount of relative damage.<br>
<br>
Imagine the screams from the monks rangers and rogues when they wake up after next patch and find out they are only doing about 1300 per round like we do post 50. Oh what a horrible thing that we would all do a similar amount of damage (albeit unsing different methods) to the mobs.  I mean, how would you then select who to group?  A delimma of Epic proportions would ensue from the chaos of choosing groups from a mob of balanced damage doers.<br>
<br>
/sarcasm off <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samuellandreievich>Samuell Andreievich</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 10:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can we get an enhancment that helps us get groups?</span><hr size=1> The Bane spells and Disintegrate are both level 60, how does that help lower level wizards who are trying to group for experience?<br>
<br>
As for the Anchor spells, mob gating isn't really a big enough problem for groups to go wizard hunting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=433.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=433.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=433.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=433.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=433.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=433.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option v